Dr. Jill Biden, wife of Vice President Joseph Biden, announced her plans to continue teaching by working as an adjunct professor at Northern Virginia Community College. She will be teaching two English courses this semester. Dr. Biden has been an educator for over 28 years, previously teaching English Composition at Delaware Technical & Community College. She earned two master's degrees and a doctorate in education. In addition to teaching, Dr. Biden is committed to promoting quality education and its importance to the nation's economic well-being and communities. She recently welcomed over 200 DC Public School students to the Vice President's residence as her first guests.